-- In the following assignment statements a Quadruple value
-- is used whenever there is no name assigned to that value
-- in the code table.  If there is a name assigned to the value
-- in the code table then that name is used instead of the Quadruple.
-- For instance, in
--
--   BasicArabic ::= BMPString (FROM({0, 0, 6, 0}..arabicSukun))
--
-- the Quadruple {0, 0, 6, 0} is used because there is no name for it,
-- and arabicSukun is used because the upper bound of the BasicArabic
-- alphabet, {0, 0, 6, 82}, is given the name arabicSukun in the code
-- table.
-- Collections of characters
